.nh
.TH g2
Some Gentoo CLI tools I wrote for myself.

.SH Manifest Tools
\fBg2\fR includes a set of tools for working with Gentoo \fBManifest\fR files.

.SS \fBmanifest\fR
The \fBmanifest\fR command group handles operations related to Manifest files.

.SS \fBupsert-from-url\fR
Updates or inserts a \fBManifest\fR entry for a file downloaded from a URL. This command streams the file, calculates the specified checksums, and updates the \fBManifest\fR file in the specified directory (or specific file path).

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP

.EX
g2 manifest [flags] upsert-from-url <url> <filename> <manifestFileOrDir>
.EE

.PP
\fBArguments:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<url>\fR: The HTTP/HTTPS URL of the file to download.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<filename>\fR: The filename to record in the \fBManifest\fR (typically the distfile name).
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<manifestFileOrDir>\fR: The path to the \fBManifest\fR file or the directory containing it (e.g., the ebuild directory).

.PP
\fBFlags:\fP

.PP
The following flags control which checksums are calculated. Note that \fBBLAKE2B\fR and \fBSHA512\fR are enabled by default.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-blake2b\fR (default: \fBtrue\fR): Calculate BLAKE2B checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-blake2s\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate BLAKE2S checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-md5\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate MD5 checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-rmd160\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate RMD160 checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-sha1\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate SHA1 checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-sha256\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate SHA256 checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-sha3_256\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate SHA3-256 checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-sha3_512\fR (default: \fBfalse\fR): Calculate SHA3-512 checksum.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-sha512\fR (default: \fBtrue\fR): Calculate SHA512 checksum.

.PP
\fBExample:\fP

.PP
To download a package, calculate SHA256 in addition to defaults, and update the Manifest in the current directory:

.EX
g2 manifest -sha256=true upsert-from-url https://example.com/software-1.0.tar.gz software-1.0.tar.gz .
.EE

.SS \fBverify\fR
Verifies the \fBManifest\fR against the actual ebuild files.

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP

.EX
g2 manifest verify [location]
.EE

.SS \fBclean\fR
Cleans up unused entries from the \fBManifest\fR file.

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP

.EX
g2 manifest clean [location]
.EE

.SH Metadata Tools
\fBg2\fR includes tools to manage \fBmetadata.xml\fR files.

.SS \fBmetadata\fR
Commands relating to modifying \fBmetadata.xml\fR files.

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP

.EX
g2 metadata [flags] [location]
.EE

.PP
\fBFlags:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-force\fR: Force overwrite if type mismatches or other errors
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-l, -longdescription <string>\fR: Set long description
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-m, -maintainer, -maintainer-add <email[:name[:type]]>\fR: Add/Update maintainer
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-maintainer-remove <email>\fR: Remove maintainer
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-u, -upstream-id, -upstream-add <type:id>\fR: Add upstream remote ID
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-upstream-remove <type:id>\fR: Remove upstream remote ID
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-use, -use-add <name:description>\fR: Add/Update USE flag
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-use-remove <name>\fR: Remove USE flag

.PP
\fBExample:\fP

.PP
Add a maintainer to \fBmetadata.xml\fR:

.EX
g2 metadata -maintainer-add "dev@example.com:Developer Name:person" .
.EE

.PP
Add a USE flag description:

.EX
g2 metadata -use-add "custom-flag:Enables a custom feature" .
.EE

.SH Ebuild Tools
Tools for working with \fB\&.ebuild\fR files.

.SS \fBebuild\fR
\fBSubcommands:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBinit <template_name>\fR: Initialize an ebuild from a template.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBtemplates\fR: Manage ebuild templates.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBsh-parse-to-json <ebuild_file>\fR: Parse an ebuild using the shell parser and output JSON.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBas-json <ebuild_file>\fR: Parse an ebuild using the native parser and output JSON.

.PP
\fBUsage Examples:\fP

.PP
Parse an ebuild natively into JSON format:

.EX
g2 ebuild as-json my-package-1.0.ebuild
.EE

.PP
Initialize a new ebuild from the generic template:

.EX
g2 ebuild init generic my-new-package-1.0.ebuild
.EE

.SH Site Generation
\fBg2\fR can generate a static HTML website representing your Gentoo overlay, including categories, packages, metadata, and git commit history. It also supports aggregating multiple remote overlays.

.SS \fBoverlay site generate\fR
Generates a static site for a single overlay.

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP

.EX
g2 overlay site generate [-out <dir>] [-clear] [<location>]
.EE

.PP
\fBArguments:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<location>\fR: Path to the overlay directory, or a Git URL (defaults to \fB\&.\fR).

.PP
\fBFlags:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-out\fR: Output directory for the generated site (default: \fBsite_out\fR).
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-clear\fR: Clear output directory before generation.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-fast-git-modtime\fR: Use fast (O(1)) but potentially less reliable go-git file log lookup.
.IP \(bu 2
\fB-recent-duration\fR: Duration to consider an update 'recent' (e.g., 3mo, 14d, 72h) (default "3mo").

.PP
\fBExample:\fP

.EX
g2 overlay site generate -out my_site_dir .
.EE

.SS \fBoverlay ebuild\fR
Tools to modify the overlay with ebuilds.

.PP
\fBSubcommands:\fP
*   \fBmove <from> <to>\fR: Record a package move in profiles/updates.
*   \fBslotmove <package> <from> <to>\fR: Record a slot move in profiles/updates.
*   \fBinstall [-category <string>] <ebuild.ebuild> [overlay_path] [-- <files...>]\fR: Install an ebuild into the overlay, optionally providing a specific category or additional files for the \fBfiles/\fR directory. Automatically triggers manifest, cache, use desc, and pkg_desc_index generation.

.PP
\fBExample:\fP

.PP
Install a package into a specific category with some files:

.EX
g2 overlay ebuild install -category sys-apps my-app-1.0.ebuild . -- app.conf app.service
.EE

.SS \fBoverlays site generate\fR
Generates an aggregated static site for multiple remote repositories from a \fBrepositories.xml\fR file.

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP

.EX
g2 overlays site generate [-out <dir>] [-clear] <repositoriesFile>
.EE

.PP
\fBArguments:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<repositoriesFile>\fR: Path or URL to a Gentoo \fBrepositories.xml\fR file, or \fB-\fR for stdin.

.SS \fBsite serve\fR
Serves the generated static site locally for previewing.

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP

.EX
g2 site serve [-port <int>] [path_to_overlay]
.EE

.PP
\fBExample:\fP

.EX
g2 site serve -port 8080 .
.EE

.SH Linting
\fBg2\fR provides linting to ensure overlay consistency.

.SS \fBlint\fR
Checks the repository for errors such as ebuild \fBIUSE\fR variables missing in \fBmetadata.xml\fR and missing \fBmd5-cache\fR files.

.PP
\fBUsage:\fP

.EX
g2 lint [<location>]
.EE

.PP
\fBArguments:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fB<location>\fR: Path to the overlay directory (defaults to \fB\&.\fR).

.PP
\fBExample:\fP

.EX
g2 lint /var/db/repos/my-overlay
.EE

.SH USE Flag Tools
Manage and discover USE flags, \fBuse.desc\fR, and \fBuse.local.desc\fR\&.

.SS \fBuse\fR
\fBSubcommands:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdiscover [location]\fR: Discover USE flags from ebuilds and \fBmetadata.xml\fR to regenerate \fBuse.desc\fR, \fBuse.local.desc\fR, and \fBmetadata.xml\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdesc-add <name> <description>\fR: Add a USE flag description to \fBuse.desc\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdesc-remove <name>\fR: Remove a USE flag description from \fBuse.desc\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdesc-edit <name> <description>\fR: Edit a USE flag description in \fBuse.desc\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBdesc-list\fR: List all USE flag descriptions from \fBuse.desc\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBlocal-desc-add <pkg> <name> <description>\fR: Add a USE local flag description to \fBuse.local.desc\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBlocal-desc-remove <pkg> <name>\fR: Remove a USE local flag description from \fBuse.local.desc\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBlocal-desc-edit <pkg> <name> <description>\fR: Edit a USE local flag description in \fBuse.local.desc\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBlocal-desc-list\fR: List all USE local flag descriptions from \fBuse.local.desc\fR\&.

.PP
\fBExample Usage:\fP

.PP
Discover and populate USE flags automatically:

.EX
g2 use discover .
.EE

.PP
List all local USE descriptions:

.EX
g2 use local-desc-list
.EE

.SH Cache Tools
Manage \fBmd5-dict\fR cache files.

.SS \fBcache\fR
\fBSubcommands:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBverify [location]\fR: Verify cache exists for ebuilds.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBgenerate [location]\fR: Generate cache for ebuilds.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBset-method <method>\fR: Set the cache method in \fBlayout.conf\fR\&.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBlist-methods\fR: List available cache methods.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBclean [location]\fR: Clean up unused cache entries.

.PP
\fBExample Usage:\fP

.PP
Generate the ebuild cache for the current overlay:

.EX
g2 cache generate .
.EE

.SH Package Description Index
Tools relating to generating and verifying \fBpkg_desc_index\fR\&.

.SS \fBpkg-desc-index\fR
\fBSubcommands:\fP
.IP \(bu 2
\fBgenerate [location]\fR: Generate \fBpkg_desc_index\fR file from the repository.
.IP \(bu 2
\fBverify [location]\fR: Verify existing \fBpkg_desc_index\fR file matches the repository.

.PP
\fBExample Usage:\fP

.PP
Generate the package description index for the current overlay:

.EX
g2 pkg-desc-index generate .
.EE

.SH GitHub Action
You can use the g2 GitHub Action
\[la]https://github.com/arran4/g2\-action\[ra] to integrate \fBg2\fR into your CI/CD workflows. It automatically downloads and installs \fBg2\fR for use in your workflow steps.

.SS Example Usage
.EX
name: Example workflow
on: [push]

jobs:
  build:
    runs-on: ubuntu-latest
    steps:
      - uses: actions/checkout@v4

      - name: Install g2
        uses: arran4/g2-action@v1
        with:
          # Optional: specify a version. Defaults to 'latest'
          version: 'latest'

      - name: Use g2
        run: |
          g2 lint .

      - name: Use g2 Action
        uses: arran4/g2-action@v1.2
        with:
          # Optional: specify an action
          action: 'lint .'
          # Optional: skip installation if already installed
          mode: 'run'
.EE

.SS Search Features
\fBg2 site\fR features a fully integrated browser-side search accessible from the main dashboard.
Search indexes are emitted automatically to \fBsearch/data\fR\&.
Users can query package names, descriptions, use flags, and numerous field filters (\fBcategory\fR, \fBlicense\fR, \fBmask\fR, \fBversion\fR, \fBdepends\fR, etc.).
Advanced queries support boolean logic (AND, OR, NOT), grouping \fB()\fR, and sequence matching (\fB\&'sequence of words'\fR).
Gentoo version ordering is natively supported for range queries like \fBversion:>1.2.3\fR\&.
